{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1007,"text":"When I was a child growing up in Maine,"},{"time":3166,"text":"one of my favorite things to do"},{"time":5190,"text":"was to look for sand dollars\non the seashores of Maine,"},{"time":8238,"text":"because my parents told me\nit would bring me luck."},{"time":10968,"text":"But you know, these shells,\nthey're hard to find."},{"time":13670,"text":"They're covered in sand,\nthey're difficult to see."},{"time":16729,"text":"However, over time,\nI got used to looking for them."},{"time":20197,"text":"I started seeing shapes"},{"time":21824,"text":"and patterns that helped me\nto collect them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25855,"text":"This grew into a passion\nfor finding things,"},{"time":29180,"text":"a love for the past and archaeology."},{"time":31545,"text":"And eventually, when I started\nstudying Egyptology,"},{"time":34878,"text":"I realized that seeing\nwith my naked eyes alone wasn't enough."},{"time":39291,"text":"Because all of the sudden, in Egypt,"},{"time":42164,"text":"my beach had grown\nfrom a tiny beach in Maine"},{"time":45783,"text":"to one eight hundred miles long,"},{"time":47894,"text":"next to the Nile."},{"time":49469,"text":"And my sand dollars had grown\nto the size of cities."},{"time":54254,"text":"This is really what brought me\nto using satellite imagery."},{"time":57397,"text":"For trying to map the past,\nI knew that I had to see differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61880,"text":"So I want to show you an example\nof how we see differently"},{"time":65262,"text":"using the infrared."},{"time":66903,"text":"This is a site located\nin the eastern Egyptian delta"},{"time":69880,"text":"called Mendes."},{"time":71101,"text":"And the site visibly appears brown,"},{"time":74101,"text":"but when we use the infrared"},{"time":76331,"text":"and we process it, all of the sudden,"},{"time":79005,"text":"using false color,"},{"time":80545,"text":"the site appears as bright pink."},{"time":82664,"text":"What you are seeing"},{"time":84100,"text":"are the actual chemical changes\nto the landscape"},{"time":87425,"text":"caused by the building\nmaterials and activities"},{"time":90941,"text":"of the ancient Egyptians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93385,"text":"What I want to share with you today"},{"time":95520,"text":"is how we've used satellite data"},{"time":98345,"text":"to find an ancient Egyptian city,"},{"time":100824,"text":"called Itjtawy,"},{"time":102466,"text":"missing for thousands of years."},{"time":104705,"text":"Itjtawy was ancient Egypt's capital"},{"time":107800,"text":"for over four hundred years,"},{"time":109347,"text":"at a period of time\ncalled the Middle Kingdom,"},{"time":111689,"text":"about four thousand years ago."},{"time":113624,"text":"The site is located\nin the Faiyum of Egypt,"},{"time":116553,"text":"and the site is really important,"},{"time":118176,"text":"because in the Middle Kingdom\nthere was this great renaissance"},{"time":121198,"text":"for ancient Egyptian art,\narchitecture and religion."},{"time":124784,"text":"Egyptologists have always known\nthe site of Itjtawy"},{"time":127561,"text":"was located somewhere near the pyramids\nof the two kings who built it,"},{"time":132015,"text":"indicated within the red circles here,"},{"time":134553,"text":"but somewhere within\nthis massive flood plain."},{"time":136871,"text":"This area is huge --"},{"time":138179,"text":"it's four miles by three miles in size."},{"time":141299,"text":"The Nile used to flow\nright next to the city of Itjtawy,"},{"time":144172,"text":"and as it shifted and changed\nand moved over time to the east,"},{"time":147609,"text":"it covered over the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149466,"text":"So, how do you find a buried city"},{"time":153331,"text":"in a vast landscape?"},{"time":155473,"text":"Finding it randomly\nwould be the equivalent"},{"time":157958,"text":"of locating a needle in a haystack,"},{"time":159680,"text":"blindfolded, wearing baseball mitts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161554,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162806,"text":"So what we did is\nwe used NASA topography data"},{"time":166092,"text":"to map out the landscape,\nvery subtle changes."},{"time":169218,"text":"We started to be able to see\nwhere the Nile used to flow."},{"time":172933,"text":"But you can see in more detail,\nand even more interesting,"},{"time":175742,"text":"this very slight raised area"},{"time":177813,"text":"seen within the circle up here"},{"time":179274,"text":"which we thought could possibly be\nthe location of the city of Itjtawy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183233,"text":"So we collaborated\nwith Egyptian scientists"},{"time":186272,"text":"to do coring work, which you see here."},{"time":188422,"text":"When I say coring, it's like ice coring,"},{"time":190614,"text":"but instead of layers of climate change,"},{"time":192573,"text":"you're looking for layers\nof human occupation."},{"time":194929,"text":"And, five meters down,"},{"time":196690,"text":"underneath a thick layer of mud,"},{"time":198841,"text":"we found a dense layer of pottery."},{"time":202293,"text":"What this shows is that\nat this possible location of Itjtawy,"},{"time":205191,"text":"five meters down,"},{"time":206452,"text":"we have a layer of occupation\nfor several hundred years,"},{"time":209301,"text":"dating to the Middle Kingdom,"},{"time":210722,"text":"dating to the exact period of time\nwe think Itjtawy is."},{"time":214126,"text":"We also found work stone --"},{"time":216738,"text":"carnelian, quartz and agate"},{"time":218896,"text":"that shows that there was\na jeweler's workshop here."},{"time":221357,"text":"These might not look like much,"},{"time":222866,"text":"but when you think\nabout the most common stones"},{"time":225539,"text":"used in jewelry from the Middle Kingdom,"},{"time":228933,"text":"these are the stones that were used."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230742,"text":"So, we have a dense layer of occupation"},{"time":232950,"text":"dating to the Middle Kingdom at this site."},{"time":234975,"text":"We also have evidence\nof an elite jeweler's workshop,"},{"time":237800,"text":"showing that whatever was there\nwas a very important city."},{"time":241554,"text":"No Itjtawy was here yet,"},{"time":243498,"text":"but we're going to be\nreturning to the site"},{"time":245523,"text":"in the near future to map it out."},{"time":247601,"text":"And even more importantly,"},{"time":249276,"text":"we have funding to train young Egyptians\nin the use of satellite technology"},{"time":253823,"text":"so they can be the ones\nmaking great discoveries as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257524,"text":"So I wanted to end with my favorite quote\nfrom the Middle Kingdom --"},{"time":262386,"text":"it was probably written\nat the city of Itjtawy"},{"time":264951,"text":"four thousand years ago."},{"time":267419,"text":"\"Sharing knowledge\nis the greatest of all callings."},{"time":269918,"text":"There's nothing like it in the land.\""},{"time":271705,"text":"So as it turns out,\nTED was not founded in 1984 AD."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277213,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280109,"text":"Making ideas actually started in 1984 BC"},{"time":285887,"text":"at a not-lost-for-long city,\nfound from above."},{"time":289165,"text":"It certainly puts finding seashells\nby the seashore in perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293023,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294199,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296653,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297834,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}